==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Urohaematin
<hw>U`ro*haem"a*tin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[1st
<ets>uro-</ets> + <ets>haematin</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>Urinary haematin; -- applied to the normal coloring
matter of the urine, on the supposition that it is formed either
directly or indirectly (through bilirubin) from the haematin of the
blood. See <er>Urochrome</er>, and <er>Urobilin</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Urohyal</ent>⟦br⟧
